pulltitle: Fix a bug in the tests and exclude the strict list in the treatment cohort prefs
pullsbody:
Multipreffer tries to reset prefs to their original values at cleanup. On the default branch, it's not possible to remove a pref from existence (or at least, I don't know of a way) so it does the best it can and sets an empty string value for prefs that don't exist in Firefox.

This PR makes sure our test expects that behavior.
pull_repo_desc: A Shield study to gather data on how ETP may affect our search volume
pull_commit_message: Ensure we expect empty-string values after uninstalling the add-on for prefs that didn't exist beforehand
